Deputy President David Mabuza paid tribute to Jabu Mabuza, who succumbed to COVID-19 related complications last week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Eskom chairperson and businessman Jabu Mabuza was laid to rest in Mpumalanga on Wednesday. A virtual funeral service was held. Mabuza succumbed to COVID-19 related complications last week. READ: Tributes pour in for Jabu Mabuza The business fraternity has paid tribute to the 63-year-old's efforts in transforming the business landscape. Deputy President David Mabuza was among those paying tribute to him. A memorial service was held for him on Monday.